  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model predicts absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device operating at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 credibility factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six factors were scoped out as epistemic gaps at MRL 5. The intended use scope — absolute hemolysis prediction in support of a 510(k) submission for a Class III implantable VAD at nominal operating conditions of 2500–5000 RPM, 3–8 L/min flow, and 60–120 mmHg pressure head — is described in the Claim and Requirement nodes. All assessed factors achieved required credibility levels under the Minimal profile assessment framework. Decision: Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-absolute-prediction",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-in-vitro-2022",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/monte-carlo-uq-ensemble-5000samples"
  ],
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/hemolysis-absolute-level-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index comparison against in-vitro measurements at 3500 RPM, 5 L/min"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/velocity-field-piv-comparison",
